1
00:01:58,583 --> 00:01:59,916
[KANAME]
Resonance...

2
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,916
No, don't do it, Dana!

3
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:24,666
Give her a real apology.

4
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,708
Now!

5
00:02:28,666 --> 00:02:32,208
[SOUSUKE] I mean it. I'm here
because you've been here for me.

6
00:02:36,791 --> 00:02:38,208
Sounds like an attacker sonar!

7
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,250
Huh?

8
00:02:43,875 --> 00:02:48,833
[alarm sounding]

9
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:08,875
I'm sorry it came to this,

10
00:03:08,958 --> 00:03:11,291
but I need you to stay
on board for a bit.

11
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:13,833
May I use your telephone?

12
00:03:13,916 --> 00:03:16,583
I hope you're planning
to hire a good lawyer.

13
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:19,000
We need to avoid a
conflict between Mithril

14
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:20,666
and the US military.

15
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:24,333
And we are the only ones
who can make that happen.

16
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:29,250
[CAPTAIN SAILOR]
Hmph.

17
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:32,375
It's like a whale that
forgot how to swim.

18
00:03:34,625 --> 00:03:36,458
[SAILOR] Toy Box changed
direction and headed north.

19
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:39,166
Speeding up to 30 knots.
Distance: two miles.

20
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:41,375
Launch tube doors
three and four are open

21
00:03:41,458 --> 00:03:44,000
and ready for launch
sequence any time.

22
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:47,083
Well? You're serious, right?

23
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:49,750
I dedicate this to
our fallen brothers.

24
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:51,666
Remember Pearl Harbor!

25
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,083
Launch number three!

26
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,583
Number three, launch now!

27
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:03,166
[DANA A.I.] A high-velocity
screw has been detected

28
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:09,333
in the water at bearing 2-9-8.
Unidentified torpedo closing in.

29
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,875
There's no more time...

30
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:13,500
Please let me have control
of the submarine now.

31
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,083
Unbind the helmsmen
and the sonar crew.

32
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,666
Uh, no.

33
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:20,208
Listen, this is the difference
between life and death.

34
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:22,458
I'm not sure if
I can avoid this,

35
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:24,625
so I'm positive that
you can't do it.

36
00:04:24,708 --> 00:04:26,750
We won't know that until I try.

37
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,375
You'll die like the rest of us.

38
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:30,166
Wanna kill yourself?!

39
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:33,208
[gasps]

40
00:04:33,291 --> 00:04:34,750
Let's see, huh...

41
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,583
The most expensive
suicide in the world.

42
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:42,166
I'm gonna die with a
multi-billion dollar submarine.

43
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:43,916
I rather like it.

44
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,250
[GAURON chuckles]

45
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:47,958
[TELETHA]
The reckless terrorism...

46
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:49,750
A deliberate surrender...

47
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:52,291
...the missile attack
on the Bunker Hill...

48
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:56,166
We've been misjudging this
man from the very beginning.

49
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:01,458
Why...? Why are
you doing this...?

50
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:05,625
Who's up for a game of chicken?

51
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:08,500
Dive to a depth of 1500.

52
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:11,791
[DANA A.I.] Warning: The order
exceeds the maximum depth

53
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:13,166
of recommended use.

54
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:16,833
I don't care. Let's go for it.

55
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:18,500
Aye, sir.

56
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:32,458
[KURZ] So what now?
If we keep going like this,

57
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:35,375
there's a very good chance
we'll end up as shark bait.

58
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:38,000
[GUEN] Don't worry.
I heard people say this ship

59
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:41,500
could outrun a torpedo
at top speed, easy.

60
00:05:41,583 --> 00:05:45,666
[KURZ] Moron. The latest
torpedoes are so fast it's sick.

61
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,875
And these are US issue.

62
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,166
So what? Who gives a damn?

63
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,708
Stop trying to bluff
your way out, okay?

64
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:56,041
Although, you know, Kurz-y,
if you come out

65
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:59,208
with your hands up now,
I may just spare your life.

66
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:00,791
[KURZ]
Go to hell.

67
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:04,625
[GUEN] I'm serious. Let's go up
to the command center together.

68
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,500
Why don't you have a talk with
Gauron and kill one of the crew

69
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:09,041
in front of his eyes.

70
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:11,958
If you do that, Kurz-y, then
you can join our little team.

71
00:06:12,041 --> 00:06:13,625
I promise he pays well.

72
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:17,333
[KURZ] Heh, that ain't cool.
It's disgraceful.

73
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:20,083
Listen, Kurz. Mithril
is a mercenary unit,

74
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:22,833
not some friends of justice.

75
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:26,333
I'm pretty sure I told you
before we're just killers

76
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:29,208
for hire. Isn't it kind
of an unwritten rule

77
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:33,416
that we work for the
customer who pays the most?

78
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,875
All the coolness and
loyalty in the world

79
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:37,958
ain't gonna buy you jack.

80
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:42,791
Come on out!

81
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:47,500
[KURZ]
Okay, my mind's made up.

82
00:06:47,583 --> 00:06:51,083
I'll kill you and
ask Tessa for a bonus.

83
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:53,250
I'll take a sexy shot
of her in a swimsuit

84
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:56,375
and sell it to the other guys on
board for 20 dollars a piece.

85
00:06:56,458 --> 00:07:00,250
If a hundred guys buy a print,
I'll make 2,000 bucks.

86
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:03,833
And here I was thinking you were
a little more clever than that.

87
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,000
It's not a matter
of how clever I am,

88
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:08,041
I'm just a practical kinda guy.

89
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:13,125
[SOUSUKE] It won't be long.
Hang in there.

90
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:20,625
Kaname, where's the key?

91
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:21,916
[KANAME]
Here it is.

92
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:24,458
[gasps]

93
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:25,625
Fits right in.

94
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,250
[SOUSUKE]
TAROS...

95
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:43,083
Looks like an older model
than the one in Arbalest.

96
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:47,250
It's not connected to any Lambda
Driver, but to Dana herself.

97
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,166
What?

98
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,000
I think I'm starting to get it.

99
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:52,125
Ah. Now I see.

100
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,208
K-Kaname!

101
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:05,750
[KANAME, TELETHA] Thank you,
Mr. Sagara. Your work here

102
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:10,208
is done now. Would you
please come and rescue me?

103
00:08:10,291 --> 00:08:14,208
[gunshots]

104
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:15,000
Ah!

105
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:16,041
[grunts]

106
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:27,458
[grunts]

107
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:31,375
[yells]

108
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:39,500
--[KURZ] Yah!
--[GUEN groans]

109
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:44,250
[KURTZ groans]

110
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,458
[gasps]

111
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,041
[GUEN groans]

112
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,625
[yelling]

113
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:08,958
[groans]

114
00:09:16,208 --> 00:09:17,166
[gunshot]

115
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:22,375
You're full of shit, Guen!

116
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:24,625
For someone like me,
that money is the same

117
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:26,416
as cheap toilet paper.

118
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:29,000
It's not even good enough
for wiping your ass.

119
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,500
Just hurts your butt
and clogs the drain.

120
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,000
[gasps]

121
00:09:33,083 --> 00:09:34,541
Really, Kurz.

122
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:38,000
You have absolutely no sense for
hand-to-hand combat, do you?

123
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:40,333
You jumped over him,
you jumped away from him,

124
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:41,666
like a street punk.

125
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:43,708
I couldn't keep watching.

126
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:47,250
So who is he?

127
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:49,916
Huh? That's... That's Guen.

128
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,125
What was he trying... to... do?

129
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:55,166
Hey, where have
you been, Melissa?

130
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:57,250
Huh? Where was I?

131
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,041
When I woke up,
I was in the clinic

132
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:03,250
and the alarm for the
evacuation drill was going off.

133
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:05,708
I didn't wanna go to the
hangar wearing nothing but this,

134
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:10,083
so I hid. Then I came here.
I saw you guys fighting.

135
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,625
[KURZ]
Ah, gotcha.

136
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:14,375
[MELISSA] I wonder if Peggy
gave me some strange medicine?

137
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,750
I have no clue what's going on.

138
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:20,041
What happened to Venom?
What about Sousuke?

139
00:10:20,125 --> 00:10:22,625
And-- Oh, I'm
still feeling dizzy.

140
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:32,500
[KURZ] Man. Where's a
camera when you need one?

141
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:41,375
[DANA A.I.] Warning: Deck 3,
corridor B has caught fire.

142
00:10:41,458 --> 00:10:45,916
Warning: C-System, number 16
discharge pipe has burst.

143
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:50,875
Warning: Abnormal noise from
barrier wall H-7 on deck one.

144
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:55,750
All right. Excellent.
Buckle up, everybody.

145
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:57,416
[GODDARD]
He's nuts!

146
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,000
[inaudible]

147
00:10:59,083 --> 00:11:02,875
[beeping]

148
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:07,625
[inaudible]

149
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:12,333
Dana! Hard rudder to port!
And throw out some decoys!

150
00:11:12,416 --> 00:11:13,625
Aye, sir!

151
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:14,916
He doesn't know anything!

152
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:18,750
[GAURON]
So, will we avoid it?

153
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,416
Can we do that?

154
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:23,250
I don't know.
It doesn't look good.

155
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:25,208
[chuckles]

156
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:33,250
[TELETHA] Dana. Launch number
one and number two

157
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:35,333
countermeasure when I
give you the signal.

158
00:11:35,416 --> 00:11:36,916
Set for deep-sea mode.

159
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,833
[DANA A.I.]
Aye, Ma'am.

160
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:38,666
[CREW]
Huh?

161
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,541
[TELETHA]
No, not yet...

162
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:44,208
[gasps]

163
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:45,750
Do it now!

164
00:11:47,083 --> 00:11:48,791
Follow with an emergency blow!

165
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,000
[growls]

166
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:51,000
[TELETHA]
Now!

167
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:52,875
[DANA A.I.]
Aye. Emergency blow.

168
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:40,666
[CAPTAIN SAILOR]
They avoided it?!

169
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:43,416
Yes. It seems they
used emergency blow.

170
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:46,541
They're rising to the surface
at a tremendous velocity.

171
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,458
But how could they
have done that?!

172
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:50,500
Shit, in that small of space?

173
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:54,833
Their captain must have balls
made of steel to pull that off.

174
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:57,750
It's certainly... something.

175
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,208
He's quite a daredevil!

176
00:13:01,958 --> 00:13:03,958
What kind of magic was that?

177
00:13:04,041 --> 00:13:06,625
Don't you understand?
It wasn't magic.

178
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:08,708
It means Dana doesn't
trust you enough

179
00:13:08,791 --> 00:13:10,958
to let you have
control of this ship.

180
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:12,708
[GAURON growls]

181
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:15,500
This ship is mine and
I'm its only captain.

182
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,583
Playtime is officially over.

183
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,208
[GAURON]
She did this?

184
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,500
Heh.

185
00:13:27,583 --> 00:13:29,916
Terrific, isn't she?!

186
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:34,375
Even if you kill me, she'll be
here to save this ship!

187
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:35,541
Furthermore--

188
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:39,083
[GAURON grunts]

189
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,375
So it's you!

190
00:13:41,458 --> 00:13:42,541
There is no escape!

191
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:44,083
Surrender now!

192
00:13:44,166 --> 00:13:48,916
You really think I would?
You should know better, Honey.

193
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,541
Well, I guess not, then.

194
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:54,000
Sgt. Sagara, shoot him now!

195
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,041
[TELETHA grunts]

196
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:11,416
[gasps]

197
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:28,375
[gasps]

198
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:34,750
[GODDARD]
Sergeant!

199
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,875
You need to unlock
the handcuffs first!

200
00:14:36,958 --> 00:14:38,791
Another torpedo is on the way!

201
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:41,375
We're gonna need to be able
to maneuver the submarine!

202
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:42,958
Yes, sir! Roger!

203
00:14:47,666 --> 00:14:50,708
[GODDARD] One head cap
bearing 2-7-8. Distance 50.

204
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:52,250
There's no way out...

205
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:57,291
[ringing]

206
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:00,375
Sousuke...

207
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:01,875
[gasps]

208
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:06,041
[KANAME] Tessa...
She told me... that you...

209
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,125
Kaname?

210
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:11,625
[KANAME] You needn't
worry about de Danaan...

211
00:15:15,166 --> 00:15:15,958
[gasps]

212
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,791
You take care of the captain!

213
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,000
S-Sgt. Sagara!

214
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,375
[gasping]

215
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:35,125
That's it... it's
the safety system!

216
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,458
[gasps]

217
00:15:36,541 --> 00:15:39,125
A US Navy surface
ship is nearby.

218
00:15:39,208 --> 00:15:41,541
They've got their submarines
set to disarm torpedoes

219
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:45,000
above a certain depth to
avoid any friendly fire.

220
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:48,625
[SAILOR] Captain expected
the second torpedo.

221
00:15:48,708 --> 00:15:51,750
And she knew exactly
what she was doing.

222
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:55,666
Put her down now!

223
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,541
Wow, what a woman!

224
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:59,333
I think we can all agree!

225
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:04,541
[SOUSUKE]
Gauron! Where are you?!

226
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:06,083
Gauron!

227
00:16:11,708 --> 00:16:13,041
Gauron!

228
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:14,125
Gauron?!

229
00:16:14,208 --> 00:16:15,666
[gasps]

230
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:17,208
[SOUSUKE]
Kaname...

231
00:16:17,291 --> 00:16:19,875
[CAPTAIN SAILOR] Son of a bitch!
We missed them again? How?!

232
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:21,916
It would appear that the
Toy Box captain knew

233
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,333
about our safety systems. Or, it
might just be a coincidence...

234
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:28,291
Shut up! Unlock the
safeties on the torpedoes

235
00:16:28,375 --> 00:16:30,250
and try it one more time!

236
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:33,916
Flood the number one and
number two launch tubes!

237
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,500
[KANAME]
He's trapped like a rat.

238
00:16:35,583 --> 00:16:39,250
His back is against the wall,
but he thrives on the pressure.

239
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:42,583
It thrills him from
deep inside his heart.

240
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:46,500
It's the bottom of the ninth.
Two outs, the bases are loaded,

241
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:50,166
and a full count. All he's
thinking about right now

242
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:53,000
is hitting the ball
out of the park.

243
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,333
[SOUSUKE]
Venom.

244
00:16:54,416 --> 00:16:58,291
That's right. He's heading
out... to the stadium!

245
00:16:58,375 --> 00:17:05,083
[CROWD cheering]

246
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:10,666
[PERSONNEL A] Go back to your
positions if you're not injured!

247
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,333
Hurry up and check
the anchor wires.

248
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:15,083
[PERSONNEL B] Man down over
here! Send a stretcher.

249
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:18,458
Take care of the wound later.
Keep the airways open.

250
00:17:18,541 --> 00:17:21,666
Listen up. Everyone, keep a
clear head. You got that?!

251
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:22,833
Right!

252
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:25,500
[grunts]

253
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:28,208
Hey, Doctor. Doctor
Goldberry, come quick!

254
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:31,250
[chattering]

255
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:35,333
[MARDUKAS] It's utterly vital
that we anchor the cargo.

256
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:42,291
I'll have to enforce these
regulations from now on.

257
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:43,750
[GODDARD]
Command center.

258
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,875
[MARDUKAS]
It's me. What's happening?

259
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,416
Is there a problem
on the bridge?

260
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,791
[GODDARD] Commander!
Thank god you're alive.

261
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:51,166
It was that terrorist.

262
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:53,958
He hijacked the AI and
took control of the ship.

263
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:57,083
But thanks to the captain,
Dana was able to recover.

264
00:17:57,166 --> 00:18:01,000
[MARDUKAS] I see. What's
happened to the terrorist?

265
00:18:01,083 --> 00:18:03,625
[GODDARD] He escaped.
He's hiding somewhere.

266
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:07,916
I was going to send the
warning over the loud speaker.

267
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,625
Commander?

268
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:13,833
[MARDUKAS] Goddard,
is the terrorist injured?

269
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:17,666
[GODDARD]
Yes, Sgt. Sagara shot him.

270
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,125
[MARDUKAS]
The left shoulder?

271
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:21,666
[GODDARD]
Yeah.

272
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,666
[MARDUKAS]
Not good!

273
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,333
Anybody, stop him!

274
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:26,458
[GROUP]
Huh?

275
00:18:26,541 --> 00:18:29,625
[MARDUKAS]
Stop the man by the red AS!

276
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,125
[gasping]

277
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:35,625
[gasping]

278
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:39,333
[screaming]

279
00:18:40,125 --> 00:18:41,125
[growls]

280
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:42,750
[MARDUKAS]
Dammit!

281
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:48,583
Take all the injured and
evacuate the hangar right now!

282
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:51,916
It doesn't matter where you go!
Just hurry up and run!

283
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:06,833
I still got it!
The power! It's mine!

284
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:13,833
[screaming]

285
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:22,791
[GAURON laughs]

286
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:23,958
Huh?

287
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:32,708
[MARDUKAS]
Huh? Is it Sgt. Sagara?

288
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:45,375
[thunder rumbles]

289
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:47,125
[MARDUKAS] He's backed
the Tuatha de Danaan

290
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:49,166
into a tight corner.

291
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:15,375
[GREY] Your mission...
Is to make it home, Sousuke.

292
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,666
[MELISSA] If you're thinking
that it's all up to you to

293
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,125
protect us along with
Kaname, you're dreaming.

294
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:30,708
[gasps]

295
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:32,708
Did I wake you?

296
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:38,833
I've... I've had enough!

297
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,125
[GAURON laughs]

298
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:47,000
I'm so delighted, my Kashim!

299
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:10,000
Kashim...

300
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:13,041
Look, Gauron, I'm sending you...

301
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:14,833
...straight to hell!

302
00:22:59,041 --> 00:23:00,791
[MARDUKAS]
We finally won the battle.

303
00:23:00,875 --> 00:23:02,541
Captain, I'm honored.

304
00:23:02,625 --> 00:23:05,375
Looking back on my 25 years
of service in the Navy,

305
00:23:05,458 --> 00:23:07,791
I've had one
hardship after another.

306
00:23:07,875 --> 00:23:10,416
[KANAME, TELETHA] Next Full
Metal Panic, the last episode:

307
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:11,708
"Into the Blue."

308
00:23:11,791 --> 00:23:14,041
[SOUSUKE]
It's time. Is everyone ready?

309
00:23:14,125 --> 00:23:15,083
[MARDUKAS]
Huh?

